metadata.description:
Serial: 59/600
Size (cm): 50 x 70

Banksy’s Pulp Fiction depicts a famous scene from the 1994 film Pulp Fiction by Quentin Tarantino. The piece depicts the two characters played by Samuel L. Jackson and John Travolta aiming their pistols off screen. Banksy's version ironically replaced their pistols with a bright yellow banana. Banksy's use of a banana is reminiscent of pop cultural references by Andy Warhol's 1967 The Velvet Underground and Monty Python's sketch “Self Defence Against Fresh Fruit”.
metadata.name: Banksy | Pulp Fiction (2004)
